Bank of America Corp To Pay $2.2 Million To Black Job Seekers-Reuters
Monday, 23 Sep 2013 06:58pm EDT
Reuters reported that Bank of America Corp was ordered to pay $2.18 million to 1,147 black job applicants over racial discrimination in hiring that kept qualified candidates from getting jobs, the U.S. Department of Labor said. The decision by Linda Chapman, an administrative law judge at the Labor Department, awards back pay and interest to former candidates for teller and entry-level administrative and clerical positions in the bank's hometown of Charlotte, North Carolina.Â 
